As I reflect on the past year I can't help but feel grateful for all the fulfillment and personal growth I've experienced. 

I got to DJ at the major music festival Lightning in A Bottle, which was a dream come true. I also landed an amazing job as a digital compositor in the visual effects industry, working on the shows See, The Peripheral, and Westworld. It feels so awesome to have two creative careers that I really love.

Throughout the year, I've made a lot of progress in my personal growth and have become more confident in sharing my music and learning to let things be good enough. I'm looking forward to another year of building my music career and developing my skills so that I can continue to move people through my art. 

Here's to a new year filled with even more growth and success!

I am excited to announce the launch of my new dance series, Echo Chamber. 

As many of you may know, I started my first series, Inner Dialogues, a few years ago. While Inner Dialogues will continue to focus on a more melodic, chill, and lounge sound that my fans have come to expect, Echo Chamber will delve into various dance genres with a bit more energy.  Can't wait for you to hear it!

I am excited to announce that I’m DJing the Underground for Folsom’s biggest party, Real Bad, on their 34th anniversary!

Music is, of course, central to Real Bad. Their DJ selection process involves elimination rounds, a blind audition, and a committee that votes on which artists represent the vibe they’re looking for, which is why it’s such an honor to be chosen. 
📸 @jprussellstudio
